<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>Just for noting</title><link>https://blog.m157q.tw/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 16 Oct 2014 08:12:00 +0800</lastBuildDate><item><title>Use screen Command to Access Serial Port</title><link>https://blog.m157q.tw/posts/2014/10/16/use-screen-command-to-access-serial-port/</link><description>&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;$ screen /dev/ttyS0 &lt;span class="m"&gt;19200&lt;/span&gt;  
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This command simply opens up a connection to serial port 0 (ttyS0) with a baud speed/rate of 19200  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
